(43, 6, 63, 48, 5, 25, 25, 'the spirit that quickeneth', 'Connection of Spirit and Life', 'This connection highlights the importance of living and walking in the Spirit as a source of life. Both passages emphasize that the Spirit is essential for true vitality and guidance in the believer''s life.', 'theme', 0.713, 'high', 'v1.2', 'gpt-4o-mini'),
(43, 6, 63, 58, 4, 12, 12, 'the words that I speak unto you, they are spirit, and they are life', 'Connection of Spirit and Word', 'This connection highlights the life-giving nature of the word of God as both passages emphasize the spirit''s role in imparting life. John 6:63 states that the words spoken are spirit and life, while Hebrews 4:12 describes the word of God as powerful and discerning, indicating its spiritual efficacy.', 'theme', 0.706, 'high', 'v1.2', 'gpt-4o-mini'),
(43, 6, 63, 19, 119, 93, 93, NULL, 'Connection of Quickening Spirit', 'Both passages emphasize the concept of being quickened or made alive. John 6:63 speaks of the spirit that quickens, while Psalms 119:93 directly mentions being quickened by precepts.', 'theme', 0.671, 'high', 'v1.2', 'gpt-4o-mini'),
(43, 6, 63, 19, 119, 130, 130, 'the words that I speak unto you', 'Connection of Words and Understanding', 'Both passages emphasize the transformative power of words. John 6:63 states that Jesus'' words are spirit and life, while Psalms 119:130 highlights that God''s words give light and understanding.', 'theme', 0.615, 'high', 'v1.2', 'gpt-4o-mini'),
(43, 6, 63, 43, 6, 68, 68, 'they are spirit, and they are life', 'Connection of Eternal Life', 'Both passages emphasize the significance of Jesus'' words as life-giving. The phrase ''words of eternal life'' in John 6:68 directly relates to the ''words that I speak unto you, they are spirit, and they are life'' in John 6:63.', 'theme', 0.615, 'high', 'v1.2', 'gpt-4o-mini'),
(43, 6, 63, 5, 32, 47, 47, 'they are spirit, and they are life', 'Connection of Life and Spirit', 'Both passages emphasize the concept of life as essential. John speaks of words that are spirit and life, while Deuteronomy describes the teachings as life itself, indicating their vital role in sustaining existence.', 'theme', 0.594, 'high', 'v1.2', 'gpt-4o-mini'),
(43, 6, 63, 60, 1, 23, 23, 'the words that I speak unto you, they are spirit, and they are life', 'Connection of Spirit and Word', 'Both passages emphasize the life-giving power of the word. John highlights that the words of Jesus are spirit and life, while Peter speaks of being born again by the word of God, which lives forever.', 'theme', 0.594, 'high', 'v1.2', 'gpt-4o-mini'),
(43, 6, 64, 43, 10, 26, 26, 'believe not', 'Belief and Unbelief in Christ', 'This connection highlights the theme of belief and unbelief in Jesus. Both passages emphasize that certain individuals do not believe, indicating a distinction between those who are part of His flock and those who are not.', 'theme', 0.34199999999999997, 'high', 'v1.2', 'gpt-4o-mini'),
(43, 6, 64, 55, 2, 19, 19, NULL, 'Divine Knowledge of Believers', 'This connection highlights the theme of God''s knowledge of those who belong to Him. Both passages emphasize that the Lord knows who truly believes and who does not.', 'theme', 0.33499999999999996, 'high', 'v1.2', 'gpt-4o-mini'),
(43, 6, 64, 58, 4, 13, 13, 'believe not', 'Knowledge of Belief and Betrayal', 'Both passages emphasize the awareness of Jesus regarding belief and betrayal. John 6:64 highlights Jesus'' knowledge of those who do not believe, while Hebrews 4:13 underscores that all things are manifest in his sight.', 'theme', 0.33499999999999996, 'high', 'v1.2', 'gpt-4o-mini'),
(43, 6, 64, 19, 139, 2, 4, 'believe not', 'Knowledge of Human Hearts', 'This connection highlights the theme of God''s omniscience in knowing human thoughts and intentions. Both passages emphasize the understanding of belief and betrayal, illustrating that God is aware of all aspects of human behavior.', 'theme', 0.32799999999999996, 'high', 'v1.2', 'gpt-4o-mini'),
(43, 6, 64, 43, 2, 24, 25, NULL, 'Knowledge of Belief and Betrayal', 'Both passages emphasize Jesus'' awareness of human belief and intentions. In John 6:64, Jesus knows who believes and who will betray him, while in John 2:24-25, it states he knows what is in man.', 'theme', 0.32799999999999996, 'high', 'v1.2', 'gpt-4o-mini'),
(43, 6, 64, 45, 8, 29, 29, 'For Jesus knew from the beginning', 'Foreknowledge and Belief', 'This connection highlights the theme of foreknowledge in both passages. John 6:64 mentions Jesus knowing who would believe, while Romans 8:29 speaks of God''s foreknowledge in predestining individuals.', 'theme', 0.32799999999999996, 'high', 'v1.2', 'gpt-4o-mini'),
(43, 6, 64, 44, 15, 18, 18, NULL, 'Divine Knowledge of Belief', 'This connection highlights God''s omniscience regarding belief and actions. Both passages emphasize that God knows all, including who believes and who does not.', 'theme', 0.321, 'high', 'v1.2', 'gpt-4o-mini'),
