(43, 6, 65, 49, 2, 8, 9, 'except it were given unto him', 'Connection of Divine Gift', 'This connection highlights the theme of salvation as a gift from God. Both passages emphasize that coming to Christ and being saved are not based on human effort but are given by the Father.', 'theme', 0.391, 'high', 'v1.2', 'gpt-4o-mini'),
(43, 6, 65, 55, 2, 25, 25, 'except it were given unto him of my Father', 'Divine Influence on Repentance', 'This connection highlights the theme of divine initiative in both passages. John 6:65 emphasizes that coming to Jesus is contingent upon what is given by the Father, while 2 Timothy 2:25 suggests that repentance is also a gift from God.', 'theme', 0.384, 'high', 'v1.2', 'gpt-4o-mini'),
(43, 6, 65, 59, 1, 16, 18, 'except it were given unto him of my Father', 'Divine Gift and Human Response', 'This connection highlights the theme of divine initiative in salvation. Both passages emphasize that coming to Jesus and being begotten by God are gifts from the Father.', 'theme', 0.356, 'high', 'v1.2', 'gpt-4o-mini'),
(43, 6, 65, 50, 1, 29, 29, 'except it were given unto him', 'Divine Gift of Faith', 'Both passages emphasize that belief and suffering for Christ are gifts from God. John 6:65 indicates that coming to Jesus is granted by the Father, while Philippians 1:29 states that believing in Him is also given to believers.', 'theme', 0.349, 'high', 'v1.2', 'gpt-4o-mini'),
(43, 6, 65, 56, 3, 3, 7, 'except it were given unto him of my Father', 'Connection of Divine Initiative', 'This connection highlights the theme of divine initiative in salvation. John 6:65 emphasizes that coming to Jesus is granted by the Father, while Titus 3:5 states that salvation is not based on human works but on God''s mercy.', 'theme', 0.349, 'high', 'v1.2', 'gpt-4o-mini'),
(43, 6, 66, 42, 9, 62, 62, 'walked no more with him', 'Discipleship and Commitment', 'This connection highlights the theme of commitment in discipleship. In John 6:66, disciples turn back, while Luke 9:62 emphasizes the necessity of not looking back once committed.', 'theme', 0.43999999999999995, 'high', 'v1.2', 'gpt-4o-mini'),
(43, 6, 66, 62, 2, 19, 19, 'walked no more with him', 'Discipleship and Departure', 'This connection highlights the theme of disciples leaving. Both passages emphasize that those who depart were not truly part of the community.', 'theme', 0.43299999999999994, 'high', 'v1.2', 'gpt-4o-mini'),
(43, 6, 66, 43, 6, 60, 60, 'many of his disciples went back', 'Disciples'' Reactions to Jesus'' Teachings', 'Both passages emphasize the response of Jesus'' disciples to his difficult teachings. In John 6:60, the disciples express their struggle with his message, leading to many turning away in John 6:66.', 'theme', 0.40499999999999997, 'high', 'v1.2', 'gpt-4o-mini'),
(43, 6, 66, 58, 10, 38, 38, 'went back', 'Discipleship and Faithfulness', 'This connection highlights the theme of perseverance in faith. Both passages emphasize the consequences of drawing back from commitment, with John noting disciples who ''went back'' and Hebrews warning against those who ''draw back.''', 'theme', 0.40499999999999997, 'high', 'v1.2', 'gpt-4o-mini'),
(43, 6, 66, 43, 8, 31, 31, 'disciples went back, and walked no more with him', 'Discipleship and Continuation', 'This connection highlights the theme of discipleship, as both passages address the commitment of followers to Jesus. In John 6:66, many disciples turn away, while John 8:31 emphasizes the necessity of continuing in Jesus'' word to truly be his disciples.', 'theme', 0.391, 'high', 'v1.2', 'gpt-4o-mini'),
(43, 6, 66, 40, 19, 22, 22, 'walked no more with him', 'Disciples Leaving and Sorrowful Departure', 'This connection highlights the theme of individuals choosing to leave or walk away from Jesus due to their attachments. Both passages emphasize the difficulty of following Jesus when faced with personal sacrifices, as seen in the disciples'' departure and the young man''s sorrow over his possessions.', 'theme', 0.384, 'high', 'v1.2', 'gpt-4o-mini'),
(43, 6, 66, 55, 4, 10, 10, 'walked no more with him', 'Discipleship and Abandonment', 'This connection highlights the theme of forsaking one''s commitment. Both passages emphasize individuals who have turned away from their previous dedication, reflecting a common struggle in discipleship.', 'theme', 0.384, 'high', 'v1.2', 'gpt-4o-mini'),
